        <p> I was able to force myself to fall asleep again, but around 4:30 a.m. was finally over. I grabbed my computer and sat down in the lobby. Steffi joined shortly before seven. She couldn't sleep anymore and was therefore already showered and ready to go out. We quickly got a tourist pass, with which we can watch 7 different attractions here in New York and at least save a lot of money. </p>
        <p> For breakfast we were in a completely unusual shop. The name was "food". It is a mixture of station snack and buffet restaurant. They have a huge selection and almost everything has the price of $ 11 per pound. No matter whether scrambled eggs, pancakes or wrap. </p>
        <p> After breakfast we made our way through the Wall Street to the new World Trade Hochh&auml;usern for the 9/11 Memorial Museum. This was the first to be on our note. It is beautiful and really extensive. It is completely underground, on the still existing and visible foundations of the two high -rise buildings that were collapsed on September 11, 2001 by terrorists with two large passenger aircraft. </p>

