        <p> The exhibition goes into detail. There are actually several parts. In one room, everyone explains how the time process was. If you want, you can even listen to what was going on at the 4th machine board that fell on the field. Recordings from the cockpit and air traffic control are alluded to and also recordings of people who tried to reach their loved ones and left news on the answering machine. That goes very close, I tell you, because this time it is already clear how it went out. For this reason, you will also find handkerchief donors every few meters. Destroyed fire engines that were hit when the buildings collapses are also available everywhere. In addition, friendly staff stands on every corner and willingly tells backgrounds and stories about the respective things where you are. </p>
        <p> After Steffi bought a nice T-shirt with the imprint "Love is Stronger Than Hate" (love is stronger than hatred), we started looking for something. On the way to the next Subway Sandwich Store, we quickly stopped at T-Mobile and still get me internet for my cell phone. Without the internet is also kind of stupid. </p>
