        <p> The afternoon dawned through the streets of Manhattan and passed Chinatown and Little Italy. Unfortunately it started to rain so that we moved into a small restaurant and first enjoyed cream br&ucirc;l&eacute;e, "Bomba" (ice cream with chocolate coating), cola and hot chocolate. Then we made our way to Macy&rsquo;s, because Steffi wanted to go to the Christmas department (Santanda). Unfortunately, nobody had told us beforehand that you had to reserve there so that we crashed into the admission control. </p>
        <p> Then we moved on to the Times Square like cast poodles and looked at the Hard Rock Cafe, Bubba Gump Shrimps and of course in the Disney Store. Here, however, our paths should separate. I still had an admission ticket for a Pentatonix concert this evening. An A-capella band from the USA. The concert was really great and in a beautiful theater (Beacon Theater), with a lot of splendor and gold. In the meantime, Steffi looked around the M&amp;M store and then drove back to the hotel. </p>
        <p> After the concert, I made my way back to the hotel. It was still raining and the wind was getting stronger. In front of the hotel I had really problems getting forward because it stormed. Well we want to hope that it will be better tomorrow. Steffi reported that the television program tells something about storm surge etc., but didn't look so bad ... let's wait! Good night. </p>
